value.name: Mount Sniktau - Wikipedia
value.snippet: Mount Sniktau is a high mountain summit in the Front Range of the Rocky Mountains of North America. The 13,240-foot (4,036 m) thirteener is located in Arapaho National Forest, 1.6 miles (2.5 km) northeast ( bearing 48°) of Loveland Pass in Clear Creek County, Colorado, United States. value.name: Mount Sniktau : Climbing, Hiking & Mountaineering : SummitPost
value.snippet: Mount Sniktau | RyanS. Among the top 500 highest peaks in Colorado, Mount Sniktau is a popular outing for those starting to cut their teeth on winter summit attempts in the Colordo highcountry. Ready access from Loveland Pass via US Hwy 6 makes reaching the summit of the peak a relatively short and painless jaunt in any season.

value.name: Mt. Sniktau Hike at Loveland Pass - Day Hikes Near Denver
value.snippet: Mt. Sniktau may be the most accessible and breathtaking summit hike near Denver. This 4-miles, moderate hike up to Sniktau travels across high country tundra along ridgelines with views of Grays and Torrey peaks and views of the Gore Range of mountains in the north. Considered a year-round hike this trail is popular with hikers wanting to get in ...

value.name: A Guide to the Mount Sniktau Trail | 10Adventures
value.snippet: The Mount Sniktau Trail is a demanding hike up the east side of the Continental Divide near Clear Creek County, Colorado. Leave the city in the rear-view mirror and head out into the wilderness as you climb up the Mount Sniktau Trail. The expansive mountainous views from the summit will make you forget all about your tired feet.

value.name: Mt. Sniktau Trail Hiking Trail, Keystone, Colorado
value.snippet: Due to the ease of access, the Mt. Sniktau Trail is a popular route no matter the weather. The proximity to Loveland Pass makes this an ideal spot for backcountry skiers and snowboarders in the winter months, and the large parking area and position along the Continental Divide make it a good choice in the summer.

value.name: Mt Sniktau (13,234'), Front Range - Trekking Colorado
value.snippet: Mount Sniktau sits just east of the Continental Divide on the Front Range of the Rocky Mountains. The summit is located less than a mile south of Interstate 70, and east of the Eisenhower Tunnel. Despite being close to an Interstate and being one of the windiest places in Colorado, Mt Sniktau made the list because of the epic views from the summit.

value.name: Mount Sniktau — Front Range Ski Mountaineering
value.snippet: Mount Sniktau is the massive peak that catches skiers' eyes when they are driving west on Interstate 70 at mile marker 224 near the town of Silver Plume. The mountain is viewed by many, climbed by many, but skied from the summit to I-70 by few. Sniktau is a highly accessible mountain as it is connected directly to the popular Loveland Pass.

value.name: Mount Sniktau - GO HIKE COLORADO
value.snippet: Mount Sniktau is a relatively simple 13er and an excellent early summer high altitude hike. The hike itself is easy to follow and the access doesn't require 4WD or dirt roads. A hike this amazing shouldn't be so simple. From Loveland Pass head up the steps on the east side of the pass.
